// NB codeswitch corpus — SC-04 Phase 4, NEW fixture file (Plan 04-03).
//
// Each case contains a contiguous span of >=3 non-Norwegian tokens inside
// NB surrounding text. Expected is either `[]` (full suppression, SC-04
// acceptance criterion #3 "at most 1 flag per paragraph") or a single
// finding on a real Norwegian typo outside the codeswitched span.
//
// The `nb-codeswitch.js` rule (priority 1) populates ctx.suppressed for
// every token index inside a dense unknown-to-NB-AND-NN window; the
// finding-emitting rules honor ctx.suppressed with a one-line early exit.
// MIN_TOKENS=8 gate prevents short mixed greetings from triggering
// density suppression (Pitfall 8).
//
// Runner auto-discovers `fixtures/{lang}/*.jsonl` files — no edit to
// `scripts/check-fixtures.js` needed when adding this NEW file.
//
// Authoring notes (Plan 04-03):
//   - Ich, Guten, Bonjour, Morgen etc. are mid-sentence-capitalized and
//     the density predicate's isLikelyProperNoun filter excludes them
//     from the unknown count (Pitfall 2) — so German cases with capital
//     nouns often fall below the 3-unknowns-in-5 threshold and suppress
//     less aggressively than a superficial reading would suggest. The
//     cases below use LOWERCASE English/French phrases to exercise the
//     density heuristic as actually specified; German cases that rely on
//     capitalized nouns are tracked as deferred-issues for Plan 04-02's
//     acknowledged tuning window.

